In the Third Book, the question is broached, how we are to act in case of a conflict between the honestum and the utile, i. e. between that which is good in itself and abstractedly, and that which is good in reference to external objects. Panaetius himself had intended to answer this question, but he did not fulfil his intention (111 2, 7).
